Supplementary Information 3 - Global annual average landings of sharks and rays (Sharks MOU Annex-I listed, Non-listed and Uncertain) reported to FAO (2015-2019)

\(~\)

\(~\)

Each FAO area tab has two plots and a table representing the total landings of:

  • shark and ray species listed under Annex 1 of Sharks MOU (Shars MOU)
  • shark and ray species that are not listed under Annex 1 of Sharks MOU (Non Sharks MOU).
  • the total landings that may contain listed and non-listed species (Uncertain)

Within each table, the contribution of each broad species category to the total number of reported uncertain landings is displayed after the “Uncertain” column. The numbers displayed at the last column of the table represent the yearly average of all shark and ray species reported as landed (Sharks MOU, Non Sharks MOU and Uncertain).

The first plot includes the top three nations reporting the highest landings, as can be seen in Figure 3 of the meeting document. The second plot represents a close up of the landings reported from the remaining nations as it is seen at the fourth bar within the plots presented in Figure 3. Note the scale between the two plots is different.

Colour of nations within plots indicate Sharks MOU and CMS Status: (Dark blue) Sharks MOU Signatory and CMS Party; (light blue) Sharks MOU Signatory only; (green) CMS Party only; (grey) range state. Note that not all colours may be present in any given plot.
